  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "This was by the end of March 1944.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[BEEP]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Can I stop?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So we arrived safely in Bucharest, which was already flooded with thousands and thousands of refugees from Moldavia.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The only address that we had in Bucharest was my uncle, my father's brother, who moved in Bucharest before the pogrom.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Maybe he had a feeling that is going to happen, something ugly in Iasi.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They were living, he, his wife, and my cousin, in a one-bedroom flat.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So the whole Fliss family of Iasi landed in this little place, and we stayed there with them for about two weeks, about I would say 20 people sleeping on the floor to the despair of my aunt, who was a very fussy person.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Eventually, we managed to get a flat.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We arrived in Bucharest with one suitcase, the three of us.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we managed to get the flat.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My father bought a bed, which was the most important thing to have for the three of us to sleep in, all three in one bed, and one table-- no chairs.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The situation was very poor because Romania as a German ally was taking a big beating from the Russians.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So not even a month passed, and the big bombings-- American and British bombings-- started in Bucharest.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Large fleets of aircraft of bombers came from Italy, from the front of Italy, to Romania because Romania was the main supplier of fuel, of petrol, to the German army, and the source of this precious [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] commodity was 60 kilometers north of Bucharest, in Ploesti, P-L-O-E-S-T-I, Ploesti.",
      "word_count": 51
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And while bombing Ploesti, they were also bombing Bucharest.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
